# Scenario: MARGINAL SIGNAL (Nordic dialect) — Nordic nRF9160 in a
# warehouse-rack deployment with poor RF.
# Same fault class as fixture 06 but Nordic uses +CESQ for signal reporting
# rather than +RSRP / +QCSQ / +UCGED. Tests whether the marginal_signal rule
# generalizes — likely a GAP since the rule's RSRP detection only handles
# the +RSRP and +QCSQ formats, not +CESQ.
# Expected SE diagnosis: marginal RF — RSRP at edge of LTE-M sensitivity.
# +CESQ values: rxlev=99 (n/a), ber=99 (n/a), rscp=255 (n/a), ecno=255 (n/a),
# rsrq=15 (-13.0 dB), rsrp=23 (corresponds to -118 dBm — at the cliff).
# Customer guidance: improve antenna placement, use higher-gain external
# antenna, consider switching to NB-IoT for better link budget.

